               , they assume that the true state is (−e, −d). This belief will prevent any deviation that results in an order flow that is out of an equilibrium path. It is also straightforward to verify that the informed trader will not deviate from the current strategy in the state of (e,d) and (−e, −d) because these are the two states in which he makes the highest profit: a deviation only reduces his profit.

